1 Download ISO From Debian 3.1 M68K https://cdimage.debian.org/mirror/cdimage/archive/3.1_r8/m68k/iso-cd/
2 Then flash iso
3 Setup Debian 3.1
4 After Debian Configuration finished and skip configure apt click Finish configuring the base system then login as root
5 Run nano /etc/apt/sources.list
  Then add this archive below

  deb http://archive.debian.org/debian sarge main contrib non-free
  deb-src http://archive.debian.org/debian sarge main contrib non-free

  deb http://archive.debian.org/debian-security sarge/updates main contrib non-free
  deb-src http://archive.debian.org/debian-security sarge/updates main contrib non-free

After adding this ctrl x y enter then apt-get update

6 Run apt-get install sudo then nano /etc/sudoers Then on User privilege specification add yourusername
  Example
  root  ALL=(ALL) ALL
  user  ALL=(ALL) ALL

then ctrl x y enter then logout then type exit then login to yourusername the after login to yourusername run sudo apt-get upgrade

7 Run sudo nano /etc/debian_version then change 3.1 To 4.10
8 Run sudo nano /etc/issue Then change Debian GNU/Linux 3.1 \n \1 To Ubuntu 4.10 \n \1 then sudo nano /etc/issue.net then change Debian GNU/Linux 3.1 %h To Ubuntu 4.10 %h
9 Run sudo rm /etc/motd then sudo reboot then sudo nano /boot/grub/menu.lst then Change Every title from End default options from Debian GNU/Linux To Ubuntu No update-grub GRUB Legacy often updates directly without needing update-grub
